{
  "text": "Roughly half of the identi\ufffded tau mutations associated with FT\ufffdP-17 affect the alternative splicing of exon 10 (reviewed in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ) ( Figure  4) . While a number of these are intronic mutations near the exon 10 5 \u2032 splice site, others are mutations in the coding region of exon 10. Virtually all of these mutations lead to an increased inclusion of exon 10 and therefore an increase in the 4R-to-3R ratio.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "23603956",
